# Licensing for github-action/

While this directory lives in the contentRX monorepo it is governed by
the **root LICENSE** ([Functional Source License, FSL-1.1-MIT](../LICENSE)),
not by the standalone MIT terms previously stated here. The GitHub
Action is part of the same source-available product as the engine,
web app, and other surfaces.

## Future intent

When this directory splits to the standalone `contentrx-action`
repository for the GitHub Marketplace (BUILD_PLAN_v2 §12), the
published repo will ship under the **MIT License** so external
maintainers can fork, adapt, and contribute. The in-monorepo source
converts to MIT on the FSL "Future License" date two years after each
release.

Until that conversion, the FSL-1.1-MIT terms in the root LICENSE
govern this directory.

## Why this directory has its own LICENSE file

Reversibility insurance. This LICENSE file is the placeholder for the
plain MIT grant that activates on the Marketplace split. Don't delete
it.

---

For the operative license that applies to this content right now, see
[../LICENSE](../LICENSE).
